<p>The <code>capitalize</code> function converts a string to title case (capitalizes each word).</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'hello world' | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo 'hello world' | capitalize}</b></p>

<h2>From Lowercase</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'john smith' | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Name: <b>{echo 'john smith' | capitalize}</b></p>

<h2>From Uppercase</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'HELLO WORLD' | lower | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Fixed: <b>{echo 'HELLO WORLD' | lower | capitalize}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $email | before('@') | replace('.', ' ') | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Name from email: <b>{echo $email | before('@') | replace('.', ' ') | capitalize}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'the quick brown fox' | capitalize | left(15){close}</pre>
<p>Truncated title: <b>{echo 'the quick brown fox' | capitalize | left(15)}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo '  spaced  text  ' | trim | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Trimmed and titled: <b>{echo '  spaced  text  ' | trim | capitalize}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Alias: <code>ucwords</code> provides the same functionality.</p>
